DictIsItemKeepsNoOrder
/ A dict is `: item` AND still rejects ordering — `item` carries no IOrderableValue
/ to leak in. sort over a list-of-dict is unorderable; PLang returns that as an error
/ (not a thrown exception), so the on-error handler catches it.
- set %people% = [{"name":"b"}, {"name":"a"}]
- sort %people%, on error call Caught
- assert %caught% is true

Caught
- set %caught% = true
